	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm trying to think of an acceptable way of programming software hi-res sprites on the SNES.  4bpp is more colorful than 2bpp, but it's also more taxing on the cpu and dma.  We can probably speed up code by not letting sprites overlap, and hide color limitations with attribute clashing.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


